[{"c":"<p>From heav’n You came, helpless Babe,</p><p>Entered our world, Your glory veiled;</p><p>Not to be served but to serve,</p><p>And give Your life that we might live.</p>"},{"c":"<p>This is our God, the Servant King,</p><p>He calls us now to follow Him,</p><p>To bring our lives as a daily offering</p><p>Of worship to the Servant King</p>"},{"c":"<p>There in the garden of tears,</p><p>My heavy load He chose to bear;</p><p>His heart with sorrow was torn,</p><p>‘Yet not my will but Yours,’ He said</p>"},{"c":"<p>Come see His hands and His feet,</p><p>The scars that speak of sacrifice;</p><p>Hands that flung stars into space</p><p>To cruel nails surrendered.</p>"},{"c":"<p>So let us learn how to serve,</p><p>And in our lives enthrone Him;</p><p>Each other’s needs to prefer,</p><p>For it is Christ we’re serving</p>"}]